1 Usage
*******

Create a file with environment variable definitions.  For example:

     FOO=~/foo
     BAR=$FOO/bar
     ОФИС=ДОМ
     BAZ=nosubst:FOO$BAR

   Now, set those environment variables in Emacs using ‘M-x
setenv-file’, and navigate to the file.  View your new environment
variables with ‘M-x getenv’.

   Optionally, set a default directory where you put such env files
using ‘setenv-file-dir’:

     (setq setenv-file-dir (expand-file-name "~/.env/"))


